      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can certainly help you draft a professional and kind rejection email for this Senior Developer candidate. The tone should be respectful of their time and effort, clearly stating that the decision was final without leaving room for further negotiation or follow-up questions.\n\nHere is a draft you can use:\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Senior Developer Application\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name] and for the valuable insights you shared during our discussions. We genuinely appreciated your enthusiasm and technical expertise, and we were impressed by your background.\n\nAfter careful consideration and reviewing the qualifications of all finalists, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills more closely align with our immediate project needs. This was a difficult decision, but it is one we have made with great respect for your talent.\n\nWe wish you the very best in your job search and future endeavors. We hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]\n\n***\n\n*Note: While this draft is polite, it is important to remember that in the tech industry, candidates often expect a second chance, so sending this with a",
