      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can certainly refine the email to be warmer and more specific about the candidate's hard work while acknowledging the fierce competition. Here is a revised version that strikes that balance:\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Senior Developer Application\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for the incredible effort you put into the technical assessment and our final interview rounds. We were truly impressed by your deep technical knowledge and the way you tackled complex problems during our sessions.\n\nWe want to be transparent that this round was exceptionally competitive; we received applications from a massive pool of incredibly talented people, and the caliber of candidates far exceeded our expectations. After reviewing every detail and discussing with our leadership team, we've decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience aligns slightly better with our current immediate roadmap.\n\nThis was certainly a tough decision, as we know you are a top-tier developer, and we are genuinely sorry you didn't make the cut. We wish you the very best in your next venture and hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]\n\n***\n\n*Note: Even though the email is polite, candidates often try to negotiate or ask for more time",
